Class MediaContent

java.lang.Object
com.apptasticsoftware.rssreader.module.mediarss.MetadataImpl
com.apptasticsoftware.rssreader.module.mediarss.MediaContent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Metadata
public class MediaContent extends MetadataImpl
Represents a media object that can be used to publish any type of media. It contains attributes for specifying the content URL, format, size, and other media-specific characteristics.

Example: <media:content url="http://www.foo.com/movie.mov" fileSize="12216320" type="video/quicktime" medium="video" isDefault="true" expression="full" bitrate="128" framerate="25" samplingrate="44.1" channels="2" duration="185" height="200" width="300" lang="en" />
